ce:section.ce:para:
First, a 1.0 mL DPDI solution (0.15 mM/L) was diluted into 5 mL with PBS buffer (20 mM, pH 6.5) in a 10 mL graduated tube. A certain amount of nitrite standard solution (or sample solution) was added to the test tube. After using distilled ultrapure water for cooling capacity to 10 mL, the mixture was shaken thoroughly and left to react for 10 min at room temperature prior to the fluorescence measurements. Simultaneously, the reagent blanks were acquired without addition of the nitrite standard solution or sample solutions. The fluorescence value of the emission peak at 482 nm for the test solution and the reagent blank (F

                           482
                        ) were directly recorded on a F-7000 fluorescence spectrophotometer with an excitation wavelength of 360 nm.
